defaultSummary:default&#xa0;defaultThe Government welcomes the Committee’s examination of this important issue. We recognise the significant challenges that the banking sector in 
defaultNorthern Ireland
default faces, and we are determined to work closely with the Northern Ireland Executive to help to boost bank lending to businesses. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe framework the UK Government and Northern Ireland Executive set out in our 
defaultBuilding a Prosperous and United Community
default document, announced on 14 June, sets out initiatives in this area and outlines an ongoing mechanism for addressing banking and access to finance issues in 
defaultNorthern Ireland
default. The Government’s evidence below covers each of the seven topics highlighted by the Committee. 
