defaultThe position of the staff of the former Irish Bank Resolution Corporationdefault 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Government has received a number of representations on the question of employees of the former Irish Bank Resolution Corporation, which was liquidated by the Irish Government on 7 February 2013.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe fully acknowledge the concerns of those 
defaultUK
default based employees who face redundancy as a result of this process. As a result of the representations received, 
defaultthe Foreign 
defaultand Commonwealth 
defaultOffice has discussed this issue 
defaultwith the Irish Government.
default 
defaultHowever, whilst the Government is able to pursue requests for clarification, it is important to note that the decision to liquidate the IBRC and the effect this had on employment contracts is a matter for the Irish Government. The Government does not have any jurisdiction in relation to the role currently being played by the Special Liquidators. 
